==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: c.o.d.
<hw>c.o.d.</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <fld>(Commerce)</fld> <def>an
abbreviation of <altname>collect on delivery</altname>; payment due by
the recipient on delivery; <as>as, a <ex>COD</ex> parcel</as>.</def>
<altsp>[Also spelled <asp>COD</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> collect, collect on delivery.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>c.o.d.</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: c.o.d.
<hw>c.o.d.</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <mark>abbr.</mark> <fld>(Commerce)</fld>
<def>an abbreviation of <altname>collect on delivery</altname>; a method
of payment by which goods are paid for when they are delivered to the
customer's home or place of business. Contrasted to <er>payment in
advance</er> or <er>terms</er> or <er>credit</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> collect on delivery.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cod</ent>⟦br⟧
